<STRONG><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" color="#808080" size="1">Wednesday 06-20-2001</font></STRONG>
</div>
<!-- begin message 0 -->
<a name="0">
<table align="center" border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2 width=100%>
  <tr>
	<td bgcolor="#707070" align="left">
		<font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" color="#FFFFFF" size="1">
		<STRONG>Specifics/Clarification on submission guidelines...</STRONG> []
		·· 06-20-2001 at 10:43 AM ·· ^<a href="#top">top</a></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td bgcolor="#202050">
	    <font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" size="-2"><br>
		A few people have emailed us asking for more specifics and/or clarification on what we're looking for in submissions.<p><STRONG>General Guidelines:</STRONG><p>1. We can only accept submissions in English.  The site is in English, the game is in English, and so this doesn't seem unreasonable...<p>2. Textual submissions should be made via email (to <A HREF="mailto:keeper@neriak.com">keeper@neriak.com</A>) in <STRRONG>plain text</STRONG>.  Please do not attach Word Processor (MS Word, Wordperfect, etc) documents, or any other kind of documents (including HTML).  Please simply cut-and-paste the text of your submission into the Email body. <p>3. Graphical submissions (maps, artwork, etc), should be made via normal email attachment (to the same email address as above).  Please send only JPEG (.JPG files) or GIF (.GIF files) graphics.  These are the standards for graphics on the Web so this shouldn't be a problem.  Please pay close attention to the filesize of your graphics.  If at all possible, compress them so that they are under 100k (100,000 bytes) in size.<p>4. I'm really not sure how to convey this, but...  All content needs to be "suitable" for posting.  We're not going to post anything like The Famous Story That Got That Guy Banned™.  We're sorry, but we really can't take that sort of risk.  Violence is fine, but there's a fine line that's up to our discretion.  Even hinted sexual content is fine (as in one of Szardos' stories), but again there's a fine line and it will come down to a judgement call by us and us alone.  If you're at all unsure if your submission will be accepted or not, just submit it!  The worst we will do is say "No, we're sorry, we can't use this." and that's that.<p>5. We reserve the right to edit textual submissions for spelling and grammar.  This means that if you submit a story or other textual item, and the spelling and grammar need cleaning up, we have the right to do so.  This is the only type of editing we will ever make to a submission.<p>6. Copyrights on submissions are retained by the author, and by making a submission you grant us the right to publish said work on our site for the period of six months.  After the six months has expired, you may request that your work be taken off the site, or elect to leave it (and certainly we prefer if you let us keep it on the site!).  This is a fairly standard Web submission "contract", we are just stating it up front =)<p><STRONG>Types of Submissions:</STRONG><p>These are the types of things we are looking for.<p>1. Stories.  Any stories about Everquest-related things can be submitted, so long as they fit the site; that is, are from the perspective of, or involve, evil races and/or classes.  These can be totally fictional, or can be about actual things which have happened to you in the game told in a story form.  You can also make up stories and lore to explain things in the world that are not explained by the Verant-provided Fiction.  An example of that would be the story of the origin of the glowing signs in Neriak that has been archived here since Day 1.  There are many, many examples of the types of stories we are looking for -- you need only look at our current offerings =)<p>2. Character Biographies.  We like these especially. =)  Please submit only bios of evil race/class characters; the "Foe" section of the bios is going to be removed shortly and will not be returning.  <p>3. Guides.  We love (and need!) guides.  Class Guides, Skill Guides, Travel Guides, Guide Guides, you name it!  We especially need Trade Skill Guides from evil race/class perspectives.  Szardos is working on a series of these, but it's our belief that one can never have enough information! (Even though Szardos' work is always more than perfect!).  We are missing a huge amount of guides we consider necessary: Shaman, Shadow Knight, Enchanter, Warrior, and so on.  Also, we have no Iksar, Troll, Ogre, or Evil Erudite/Human/Gnome-specific guides or information.  A big hole indeed; someone please fill it!  Guides can be either In Character or Out Of Character (though we prefer IC, we realize that with some things you need to step OOC to get things across correctly).  Quest Guides (Necro epic? SK epic? Shaman epic for evil Shaman? Rogue epic for DE Rogues? Etc...) are also highly desired!<p>4. Maps.  We have authorization to use a large collection of excellent maps (Zealott's, in fact) and will be putting those online very soon, but again... One can never have too much!<p>5. Artwork.  Any artwork you think we might like to display (and yes, this can include interesting screen shots) can also be submitted.  Please be repsectful and follow the guidelines set forth above for graphical submissions. Especially pay attention to file size. =)<p>6. Anything else? If in doubt, just submit it!  The worst we will do is say no! =)<p>Hopefully this clears things up, and again the email address for submissions (and questions, suggestions, etc) is <A HREF="mailto:keeper@neriak.com">keeper@neriak.com</A>.<p>
		<p><font size="1">
		<STRONG>- <a href="mailto:keeper@neriak.com">The Keeper</a></STRONG></font></font></td>
  </tr>
</table><p>
