<!-- begin message 2 -->
<a name="2">
<table align="center" border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=2 width=100%>
  <tr>
	<td bgcolor="#707070" align="left">
		<font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" color="#FFFFFF" size="1">
		<STRONG>Szardos Speaks</STRONG> []
		·· 05-22-2001 at 12:52 PM ·· ^<a href="#top">top</a></font></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
	<td bgcolor="#202050">
	    <font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica" size="-2"><br>
		Szardos Speaks<p>    My Brothers and Sisters in Shadow.  I am Szardos, called the Hotspur, gentleman and rogue of the Server Tunare.  Recently, I was done a great wrong.  A miscreant posted my stories verbatim on another website without permission.  Worse, he claimed (among other things) to have been the author of the stories, asserting that he had been Szardos of Tunare and had sold the account.  I was immediately alerted by the most excellent Keepers of this site, and the miscreant and his flimsy lies were refuted and sent packing.  Make no mistake.  My work is protected and not to be used without express permission.  A link to this worthy site is acceptable, but nothing more.  I <br>submit my stories and guides exclusively to this website alone, so If you see my work posted on another website, contact this site immediately, for it has been posted illegally.  If you need to contact me, a submission to the Keepers will be sufficient, for they know my true email address and, indeed, my true name.<br>    Know this, gentle readers: I created Szardos on Tunare and play him to this day.  I will never sell the account.  Szardos dies when Verant dies and takes Everquest with it and not before.  If you see me on Tunare, know that it is I and I alone.  Trust no other Szardos on any other site unless you see a post from me on this site telling you otherwise.  Likewise believe no player using the name of any of my characters except, on the Tunare Server, the characters called Bracewell the Bard, Wrathbone the Shadowknight, Oopz the Shaman (all of whom I also play) and dear Enoyna the Enchantress (played <br>by she with whom I am fortunate enough to share my life).  To speak with them is to speak with me (for Enoyna will relay any messages to me).  I also hold the EZBoard Account name of Szardos Hotspur.  I use that name alone.  If anyone posts under another name and asserts that he is me, he is lying.  It is a pity that I must take these steps to assert my rights and my identity, but the world is harsh, and such steps must needs be taken.<br>    This is a fine website, run by noble Keepers who merit your patronage and voice in their forums and libraries.  Support them and contribute to their site, for you will find that they will support you in return.  Noble Sevok, Worthy Zariu, I honor you for your friendship and loyalty.<p>May the shadows be kind to you all, my brethren.<p>I remain,<p>The Sole and True<p>Szardos Hotspur,<p>As of this writing, a<br>Gentleman & Rogue of the Twenty-Second Circle of Mastery<br>Tunare<p>My way is Shadow; My ally, Silence; My virtue, Surprise.<br>My creed? If you can't be Good, be Elegant.<br>
		<p><font size="1">
		<STRONG>- <a href="mailto:keeper@neriak.com">The Keeper</a></STRONG></font></font></td>
  </tr>
